Bulgarian President Arrives to Strengthen Economic Ties 
Bulgarian President Zhelyu Zhelev arrived Sunday for a four-day visit
aimed at strengthening economic ties with South Korea.
Zhelev is the first Bulgarian head of state to visit since the two
nations established diplomatic ties in 1990.
He is to confer with President Kim Young-sam and other government
leaders, tour industrial sites and meet with business leaders on
investment and trade opportunities.
Two-way trade last year came to dlrs 54 million, with South Korea
exporting dlrs 32 million worth of autos and home electronic goods.
